---
import { Plus, Minus } from 'lucide-react';
---

<section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Get answers to common questions about Legionella schematic drawings and our CAD services
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Items -->
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              What is a Legionella schematic drawing?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            A simple but accurate diagram that maps out a building's water systems, including the location 
            of pipes, tanks, outlets, and equipment. It's a crucial component of Legionella risk assessments, 
            helping pinpoint potential sources of Legionella bacteria growth and transmission.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              Why are these drawings important for health and safety?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            They visualize potential problem areas within water systems, aiding in targeted prevention 
            and control measures. They're essential for compliance with health and safety regulations, 
            demonstrating due diligence in safeguarding building occupants.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              What should be included in a schematic drawing?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <div class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>All water systems within the building, such as hot and cold water systems, cooling towers, and other potential Legionella habitats.</p>
            <p>Location of all water outlets, like taps, showers, and other sources.</p>
            <p>Regular updates to reflect any changes to the water system, ensuring its accuracy over time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              What is a water system drawing?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            A detailed diagram providing a comprehensive overview of the building's water system, including 
            the layout of pipes, tanks, and outlets. It complements Legionella schematic drawings by offering 
            a more in-depth view of the system's complexities.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              What is a Legionella schematic drawing company?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            A specialized company that creates accurate and easy-to-understand schematic drawings for 
            Legionella risk assessments. They possess expertise in various water systems and locations, 
            from complex manufacturing facilities to commercial buildings, healthcare facilities, and residential properties.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              How do I choose the right service provider?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <div class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Look for companies with accreditation from UKAS or the Legionella Control Association (LCA), 
            ensuring their competence and adherence to best practices.</p>
            <p>Seek professionals with expertise in different water systems and locations, matching your specific needs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              What certifications should I look for?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            UKAS accredited Legionella consultants can conduct risk assessments and bacteria sampling. 
            The Legionella Control Association (LCA) offers certification and training for individuals 
            and companies involved in Legionella management.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="text-center mt-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-cyan-500 text-white p-8 rounded-2xl">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Still Have Questions?</h3>
        <p class="text-blue-100 mb-6">Our experts are ready to help you with your specific requirements</p>
        <a href="/contact?#contact-form" class="bg-white text-blue-600 font-semibold px-8 py-3 rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors duration-300">
          Contact Our Experts
      </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  // Add FAQ toggle functionality
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    const faqButtons = document.querySelectorAll('section button');
    
    faqButtons.forEach(button => {
      button.addEventListener('click', function(this: HTMLButtonElement) {
        const content = this.nextElementSibling as HTMLElement;
        const icon = this.querySelector('svg');
        
        if (content.style.display === 'none' || content.style.display === '') {
          content.style.display = 'block';
          icon?.classList.remove('lucide-plus');
          icon?.classList.add('lucide-minus');
        } else {
          content.style.display = 'none';
          icon?.classList.remove('lucide-minus');
          icon?.classList.add('lucide-plus');
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>